this is a deno project. I'm parsing through some ndjason logs to group and print some data
I'll help you with parsing NDJSON (Newline Delimited JSON) logs in a Deno project. Here's a basic example of how you might do this:

```typescript
// Example code for parsing NDJSON logs in Deno

// Read the file
async function parseNDJSON(filePath: string) {
  try {
    const text = await Deno.readTextFile(filePath);
    const lines = text.trim().split('\n');

    // Parse each line as JSON
    const records = lines.map(line => JSON.parse(line));

    // Group and process the data as needed
    return processLogs(records);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error parsing NDJSON:', error);
    throw error;
  }
}

function processLogs(records: any[]) {
  // Example: Group by some field
  const grouped = records.reduce((acc, record) => {
    const key = record.someField; // replace with your grouping field
    if (!acc[key]) {
      acc[key] = [];
    }
    acc[key].push(record);
    return acc;
  }, {});

  return grouped;
}

// Usage
const filePath = "./logs.ndjson";
try {
  const result = await parseNDJSON(filePath);
  console.log(result);
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Failed to process logs:', error);
}
```

If you'd like help with a specific aspect of your log parsing or have specific requirements for grouping and printing the data, please share more details about:

1. The structure of your NDJSON logs
2. What kind of grouping you want to perform
3. How you want to format/print the output

That way, I can provide more targeted assistance.
